<DOCNO> NYT20000115.0067 </DOCNO>
<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-01-15 12:12 </DATE_TIME>
<HEADER>
A6880 &Cx1f; ttc-z
u v BC-BUDGET-LADN &LR;      01-15 0307
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-BUDGET-LADN </SLUG>
  
<TEXT>
<P>
   The Los Angeles Daily News plans to move the following general
stories for use by NYTimes News Service clients, AMs and PMs of
Jan. 16 and thereafter. For questions about stories, contact the
Daily News, (818) 713-3705.
</P>
<P>
   MINORITY-ANGELS (Los Angeles) -- The success or failure of the
new CBS drama ``City of Angels,'' will help guide the future of
similar minority themed programming, a prospect that its writer and
producer do not relish. The show, with Los Angeles County-USC
Medical Center in its opening shots, is about a struggling
inner-city hospital, and is an effort by CBS to include more
minority actors and themes in its programming. The NAACP and other
minority groups say if it fails, it might sour network executives
on the idea, and a similar chance for such a high-profile minority
show might not come for years. By Steve Carney (Will move on the
``n'' California, ``a'' national and ``e'' entertainment news
wires.)
</P>
<P>
   SETTLE-COSTS (Los Angeles) -- It started out as a routine Los
Angeles police drug raid on a house in South Central on a warm
spring night in April 1997. It became a horrible case of one
mistake after another when it turned out officers raided the wrong
home. And while none of the nine people in and around the house
suffered severe injuries after police stormed in, it ended up
costing the city $851,000. The case involving Climon Hawkins has
come to take on a deeper meaning for city officials who report
judgments and settlements already are headed for a record this
financial year, which began July 1. Officials call it the Rampart
syndrome higher payouts by the city because of the mushrooming
scandal centered at the LAPD Rampart Division's anti-gang unit. By
Rick Orlov (Will move on the ``n'' California and the ``a''
national news wires.)
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
