poster is part of a recruitment campaign in New York, New Jersey
and Brooklyn communities by the Sisters of Mercy of the Americas, a
Roman Catholic order of nuns. For more than three decades, the
number of Catholic nuns in the United States has plunged to 83,000
last year from 180,000 in 1965. The result has been a draining of
resources from the many charities and institutions that the sisters
helped create. (The New York Times)
