<DATE_TIME> 2000-01-15 21:21 </DATE_TIME>
<HEADER>
A7114 &Cx1f; ttx-z
r s BC-FBN-COWBOYS-ANALYSIS-     01-15 0669
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-FBN-COWBOYS-ANALYSIS-TEX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
COWBOYS NEED TO FIND A COACH WHO CAN FIND OFFENSE
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By RAY BUCK 
c.1999 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   IRVING, Texas _ The Cowboys' fourth coach in franchise history
couldn't survive the Cowboys' 40th season.
</P>
<P>
   So Chan Gailey is gone and Jerry Jones is power-shopping for a
successor.
</P>
<P>
   But before we start looking ahead, don't you think that this
anniversary season deserves to be remembered in some special way?
</P>
<P>
   A commemorative yellow flag might be appropriate.
</P>
<P>
   The Cowboys ended their fourth decade with eight consecutive
road losses, six blown fourth-quarter leads, a league-leading 136
penalties for 1,196 yards, an offense that ranked behind
Cincinnati, Buffalo and Kansas City among others, a second
consecutive first-round loss in the playoffs, and an overall 8-9
record after a 3-0 start.
</P>
<P>
   Now, Jones is looking for Mr. Right to come in and get this team
back to a Super Bowl while Troy Aikman is still the quarterback,
Emmitt Smith is still the running back and the parts are in place,
in Jones' eyes, to make another title run.
</P>
<P>
   For Mr. Right, this means right now.
</P>
<P>
   In order to ``fix this thing'' _ Jones' words _ the Cowboys need
to start with the hiring of a coach who either knows the offense
that Jones has in mind and that Aikman has had success in running
before, or brings in an offensive coordinator who can provide this.
</P>
<P>
   While we aren't sure who will be the next coach of the Cowboys,
we do know what kind of offense the Cowboys will be running in
2000.
</P>
<P>
   It's one that Aikman and the surviving core of veterans on this
team used under Jimmy Johnson (Norv Turner) and Barry Switzer
(Ernie Zampese) to win three Super Bowls in four years (1992-95).
That was before Gailey was brought in to replace Switzer and carry
out a campaign to improve the team's image and win championships.
</P>
<P>
   In Gailey's first season, the Cowboys went 10-6 and won the NFC
East. This season, the Cowboys couldn't put together consecutive
victories during the last three months and Gailey's offense went
from the NFL's eighth best in '98 to 16th best in '99.
</P>
<P>
   The new coach will inherit a team that was inconsistent,
self-destructive and undisciplined, and drove Gailey crazy with its
inability to ``play smart.''
</P>
<P>
   Jones isn't looking for somebody who can reinvent the wheel.
Rather, he's looking for somebody who can reconstruct the offense
to better fit the existing personnel.
</P>
<P>
   Fixing the Cowboys will require:
</P>
<P>
   Aikman to become comfortable with his receivers and in total
accord with the play calling.
</P>
<P>
   Wide receivers to stretch the field and complement Raghib
Ismail. Jason Tucker seems to have that capability. Chris Brazzell
still needs to prove himself. James McKnight (August knee surgery)
is a total unknown as a Cowboy. Michael Irvin faces a career
decision.
</P>
<P>
   Tight end David LaFleur, entering his fourth NFL season, needs
to become a focal point of the offense.
</P>
<P>
   Receivers need to start running third-down routes ``beyond'' the
first-down marker.
</P>
<P>
   Receivers need to stop dropping balls.
</P>
<P>
   Players need to stop making penalties, especially the pre-snap
variety (false start, motion, illegal formation and delay of game).
</P>
<P>
   Jones said the most difficult aspect of the game today is
finding an offense that is ``really aggressive.''
</P>
<P>
   But when you find one, you generally win.
</P>
<P>
   It used to be that ``offense won games and defense won
championships,'' but that has changed. Each of the NFL's top four
offenses _ St. Louis, Washington, Minnesota and Indianapolis _ are
playing this weekend for a chance to advance to conference
championship games.
</P>
<P>
   ``We weren't one preseason, one minicamp, one game away from,
all of a sudden, this being everything we wanted it to be,'' Jones
said at the news conference to announce Gailey's dismissal.
</P>
<P>
   This is a team that needs more than just a new coach. It's a
team that needs an offense that will get everybody on the same page
again.
nn
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
